definitions.definition: Often capitalized : a person from the generation born in the last two decades of the 20th century , from around the early 1980s to the mid-1990s and who reached adulthood early in the third millennium C.E. , characterized by their familiarity with computer technology and poorer financial prospects than their parents .
A thousandth anniversary ; also, a celebration of such an anniversary.
